    "comment": "Rationale: The paper characterizes for the first time the vesicular GABA transporter.\n\nIn figure 5a light vesicles purified by differential centrifugation from PC12 cell clones stably expressing VGAT are tested for 3H-GABA uptake and show a more uptake than membranes prepared from untransfected PC12 cells.\nFigure 5c demonstrates specificity of the transporter to GABA by testing the block of 3H-GABA uptake using a series of compounds at increasing concentrations.. Experimental description: To determine biochemically whether the rat unc-47 homologue\nencodes the vesicular GABA transporter, we expressed the cDNA in\nrat pheochromocytoma PC12 cells.",
